Citation.sTitle: Densities and Viscosities of N-Formylmorpholine + Benzene, + Toluene at Different Temperatures and Atmospheric Pressures
Citation.sAbstract: Densities and viscosities for N-formylmorpholine (NFM) with benzene and toluene were determined over several temperatures at atmospheric pressure. The measurements were carried out over the whole range of mole fractions, using a vibrating-tube densimeter and an Ubbelohde viscometer. Density and viscosity data were used to compute the excess molar volumes (V E) and viscosity deviations (4e). The V E and 4e have been fitted to the Redlich- Kister equation.
